1.00	Perturbation_(geology)	Perturbation (geology)	Perturbation (from Latin: perturbare "to confuse, disorder, disturb," from per- "through" + turbare "disturb, confuse," from turba "turmoil, crowd") is a set of Pedology (soil study) and sedimentary geology processes relating to changes in the nature of water-borne alluvial sediments and in situ soil deposits over time.	
